# Polymarket API Access

The local network blocks all Polymarket API endpoints (`data-api.polymarket.com`, `gamma-api.polymarket.com`, `polymarket.com`). Direct `curl`, `requests`, or `WebFetch` calls to these URLs will fail with 503 or SSL errors.

## Rule

**Never** test, call, or verify Polymarket APIs from the local machine.

**Always** run Polymarket API calls on the EC2 instance via AWS SSM:

```bash
AWS_PROFILE=rafik aws ssm send-command \
  --instance-ids "i-0431a0aa517edf582" \
  --document-name "AWS-RunShellScript" \
  --parameters 'commands=["sudo su - ec2-user -c '\''cd /opt/polymarket-bot && .venv/bin/python3 -c \"import requests; ...\"'\''"]' \
  --region eu-west-1 \
  --output json --query 'Command.CommandId'
```

## Applies to

- Any script or code that calls `data-api.polymarket.com`
- Any script or code that calls `gamma-api.polymarket.com`
- Any `WebFetch` or `curl` targeting `polymarket.com`
- Integration tests that hit Polymarket endpoints
- Verifying API response shapes

## Retrieving output

Use `get-command-invocation` after the command completes:

```bash
AWS_PROFILE=rafik aws ssm get-command-invocation \
  --command-id "<ID>" \
  --instance-id "i-0431a0aa517edf582" \
  --region eu-west-1 \
  --query '{Status: Status, Output: StandardOutputContent}' \
  --output json
```
